Assignment 1(Method)
📝 Java Assignment: Create a Method in a Class
👩🏫 Objective:
To help students understand how to define and use methods inside a class in Java.
________________________________________
📘 Instructions for Students:
1.	Create a Java class as per the given questions.
2.	Define a method inside the class to perform the specified task.
3.	Call the method from the main() method.
________________________________________ 
✅ Assignment Questions:
Q1. Create a class StudentInfo with a method displayInfo() that prints your name, age, and grade.
Expected Output:
Name: Aman Sharma  
Age: 16  
Grade: 10th  
________________________________________
Q2. Create a class Calculator with a method addNumbers() that adds two numbers and prints the result.
Hint: Use two variables inside the method.
________________________________________
Q3. Create a class Greeting with a method sayHello() that takes your name as a parameter and prints:
Hello, Riya! Welcome to Java programming.
Replace "Riya" with your name.
________________________________________
Q4. Create a class Circle with a method calculateArea() that calculates and prints the area of a circle.
Formula:
Area = π × radius × radius
Use: radius = 7 and π = 3.14
________________________________________
Q5. Create a class SimpleInterest with a method calculateInterest() that calculates simple interest.
Formula:
SI = (P × T × R) / 100
Use values: P = 1000, T = 2 years, R = 5%
________________________________________

📌 Bonus Tip for Students:
Use this structure for every program:
public class ClassName {
    
    // method
    public void methodName() {
        // code here
    }

    // main method
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ClassName obj = new ClassName(); // object creation
        obj.methodName(); // method call
    }
}